Incident Response > [T3]: Lab - Sysmon: Blocking Executables

Block Executables using Sysmon FileBlockExecutable

In Sysmon version 14.0, a new EventType was introduced, a FileBlockExecutable event with an ID of 27.

Now with Sysmon, you can block programs writing files into the disk based on the file header and the filtering criteria.

Multiple use cases can be utilized here.

  • Office executables (word, excel, outlook, powerpoint) to drop executables.
  • Writing executables either to the User Downloads folder.


Let us write a combined rule that blocks downloading binaries into the Downloads folder for any user.

 

 

As you can see in the above screenshot:

  1. The FileBlockExecutable was set as an EventType
  2. The Rule condition matches any directory with the C:\Users and Downloads strings.
